      "sector": "education",
      "title": "Digital student credential for campus services",
      "summary": "A national university pilot lets students receive a verifiable student credential in their digital wallet. The credential proves enrollment status and can be presented to access campus facilities, exam registration, and partner discounts—without sharing a full student record. The issuer is the university; students present the credential to on-campus services and selected external relying parties via a remote or proximity flow.A national university pilot lets students receive a verifiable student credential in their digital wallet. The credential proves enrollment status and can be presented to access campus facilities, exam registration, and partner discounts—without sharing a full student record. The issuer is the university; students present the credential to on-campus services and selected external relying parties via a remote or proximity flow.",
